{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require unlimited companies to publish their accounts",
        "additional_details": "Unlimited companies are not required to publish accounts/financial reports, but can make donations of any amount to a party.\r\n \r\nUK law on political donations does not differentiate between limited & unlimited companies, stating only that firms must be \u201ca UK-registered company incorporated in the UK which carries on business in the UK\u201d to make political donations.",
        "background": "We think the government should close loopholes with robust legislation, making it a requirement that unlimited companies file accounts. Unlimited companies may be setup by non-UK residents & used for political donations, which we believe could harm democracy.",
